< Review>
This place is the bomb! I've been going to Baja Fish Tacos for 15 years now. I remember when I first started going here, I just remember telling my buddy that "this food was so good." We wanted to go every day during lunch! Even going just in the recent days I've noticed that their food hasn't changed quality or freshness. It is still just as good as the first day I went. Good customer service too, at this location.<//Review>

< review>
Wow, for $4.25 I got a "green salad" with avocado, pinto beans and rice that was a meal in itself. The Pico De Gallo from the salsa bar, cilantro and spicy onions were perfect on top and mixed in. I haven't tried anything else YET but by the looks of how crowded this place was on a Saturday night, I know it'll be one excellent thing after another. Many locals there. A family type atmosphere, kind and helpful employees, big tv's playing sports games...a true gem. I'll be headed here after my church service down the street from now on!</review>

< Rating>
5<//Rating>
< Text>
The garden salad and Ensenada fish tacos are a weekly dinner choice for my husband and me, sometimes twice a week, at least 5 years now, likely way more.

Salad is pretty large with a variety of lettuces, cherry tomatoes, onion, corn, avocado and tortilla strips if you like. The fish portion per taco is generous, 3 good size battered strips in two soft tasty corn tortillas. I split mine into 2 tacos, one fish strip each and top them with parts of the salad including an avocado slice in each and have the final fish strip in the salad. Soooooo goood</Text>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
I love Baja Fish Tacos and have been going to various locations for over 10 years. The quality and the consistency of the food is always the same. No matter how busy this place gets you always get your food reasonably quick.  They have a very good salsa bar. Their shrimp burrito and shrimp nachos are a couple of my favorite things to order. Be aware that the portions are very big. Their combo plates are too much for one person. You can share a main dish and grab an appetizer.<//review>

< review>
This is one of my favorite Mexican food places around. The chicken burrito is bomb. Great beans and rice and the salsa are all great! The red salsa is really hot and can make you sweat but man it is good!! They have the best guacamole I have had from any restaurant! Its is seasoned perfectly and helps cool your mouth after eat all that hot salsa! It is unfortunately kind of pricey for the type of food it is and I wish they would lower there prices a bit. I get the burrito combo and chips and salsa and it cost me almost $16... just too much for what it is. But the food is great!<//review>

< Text>

For a whole year they had me signed up under non-owners insurance after, the fact that I walked in verbally explained that I needed the basic insurance and they guy verbally responded that we were in agreement and he printed out a whole book where I was to sign in agreement to what I came in for. They messed up my insurance, then blamed me because apparently I must be crazy to want a non-owners insurance on a car that I own. The manager Carlos was not accountable or responsible. He pawned me off onto a young lady named Cheyenne and he tried to blame her. I guess he felt she could not defend herself. William had a charming personality but all he cared about was getting his $300 brokers fee which he lied to me and said I could make paymentson it. That was a flat out lie.  I was left broke for the month that I started the policy because although, he verbally said I could pay it in payments the paperwork he had me sign was one lump sum. I got a phone call every month saying my policy was going to be cancelled even though, I had automatic ebt set up! It was a total nightmare. I felt like I was dealing with loan sharks that were willing to and could not wait to come to your home to break your legs. I do not know why they take notes if they are not going to bother to read them. I hate this company because I had to do their job for them and I was constantly harrased. I would NEVER recommend this as a place of business unless you hate yourself. I eould be embarresed to work in such a place. I almost got into a physical fight with one of the female employees because instead of being sympathetic and acknowledging the fact that this company as a whole totally missed the mark she thought it was a big running joke. I am poor but I am not ghetto and this company as a whole is ghetto and gets a minus F if I could give them a rating. They cost me time, emotional distress, and harrased me to the point of ridiculousness. I hope nobody foolishly goes here. Truthfully they are by far too expensive. I joined a subsiderary to Farmers and I only had to pay $100 to get it started & I pay less than I paued at Cost-u-less plus I do not get harrased for absolutely no reason. Go anywhere else other than Cost-u-less on Burney in Modesto CA. They suck to the max! Even after cancelling my policy with these jerks they are still calling me!<//Text>

<Review>BUCKLE UP! I ordered pad thai for delivery. Got it in a reasonable amount of time. Unpacked the food, ready to dive in, and...something doesn't look right. If you look at the pic, there in the middle of that potential goodness is a metal twist tie. Hiding among the noodles.

So, I called to let them know I need another one. And, I'll drive it back there. The gentleman on the phone said, "No problem, I'll give you another one and your money back." Exactly what they should do. And here's where things go bad really fast.

I'm getting ready to go back and I get a call. From that guy. He asks if I'm coming in. Yes, of course, but since I had it delivered, I have to get ready. OK.

Then, after about seven minutes, while I'm on the way, I get another call. He asks where I'm at. Not far, I say. Then he asks if I want my money back or  for them to replace the food. Hmmm, didn't you just tell me what you were going to do? By the time we get nowhere on the phone, I'm there and tell him we'll finish this discussion in person.

Bottom line: he insists he never said he'd take care of the bill and the food. He gets whipped up, which gets me whipped up. I walk out of there with no food and he offers me $10! Not even close to what I had spent. To top it off, while we're in the middle of a real, live pandemic, this guy has NO GLOVES on! And he's making and serving food! What the hell?

SKIP THIS PLACE! Stay away. Plenty of great Thai places in the area that don't have a rude, ignorant proprietor who doesn't understand how to take care of a customer when HE screws up; or even how to run a safe kitchen.

Note 1: It looks like this place is listed on other review sites under a different name.

< Text>
Satay - Small portion. Flavor was good. No char on the chicken like it was made in a pan. In comparison to other less expensive places it get 2 stars.

Order was short. I ordered 2, they sent 1, which they corrected imediately.  On response to their error, they get 5 stars.

Chow mein - very bad. Noodles were mushy over cooked and no flavor. The veggies were a mix of Broccoili carrots celery and bockchoy. Some were over cooked and some were raw. That was very strange. After a few bites I put it in the waste bin. This gets 1 star.

Thai tea - good. Decent size and flavor was good. It gets 3 stars. Good but not memorable.<//Text>

Pros: Delivery fee was only $1 and arrived exactly when estimated by email. Food was warm upon delivery. Vegetable Rolls were totally unique, deep fried but not greasy with excellent plum sauce. Peanut  sauce was great.
Cons: Pad Se Eew was totally sub-par, there was no sweet sauce at all, the noodles were too soggy, not nearly enough broccoli. Peanut salad was very disappointing, just an odd combination of vegetables, sliced too thick.
Bottom line: would not order from here again.</Text>

Went around 1 p.m. today for lunch. Ordered the red curry chicken lunch special, lady didn't look too happy about that. It came with a salad which was good with the peanut sauce. I heard a microwave go off twice and after the second time my food was brought out. Let's me know my food was not made fresh at all. Could definitely tell by the way the chicken tasted. 106965954937998216342< /userid>
<name>Scott French< /name><time>1360730658377< /time><Rating>2<//Rating>< Review>
This was the first storage place in Auburn we stopped at and the people that run the place are very friendly. We took a look around and it seemed fine... decent pricing and they are located very close to where we are currently living. We decided to go with Locksley. Big mistake! I wish we would have taken the time to look around at other storage facilities in the area a bit more. After moving in about half of our stuff we noticed large pools of water accumulating on a few of our items. When we grabbed a light and checked the ceiling there was water dripping along every inch of overlapping material (that's 5 joints x 25 feet long). We brought this to the attention of the people that run the place and they acted like it was a very unique situation. When we asked around a few of the other renters as well as people at other storage facilities in the area no one was surprised. These units are some of the oldest in the area and are not insulated (at all). They will accumulate condensation on the ceiling and drip onto your items. Do not waste your time here. Even if they ruin some of your stuff they will not even return your money for the time you rented. I attempted to get my money back from the people that run the place, then the owners, then my credit card company. No luck yet. BBB will be the next stop but in the meantime I would like to save anyone else from this waste of time and money.

The bottom line is prices around town are all very similar for storage units. For basically the same price you can get a much nicer unit, with a built in light and better insulation. The Locksley units have no lights and no insulation. We moved to another storage facility nearby and even during times of much worse weather there have been no water issues. Do yourself a favor and skip Locksley Mini-Storage, they are dishonest about the condition of the facility, the units will ruin your belongings and they will do nothing to fix the problem.<//Review>

I started using Locksley Mini Storage because I had a storage unit there in 1993 and didn't have any problems with them then so I got one there again. That's Napa know how >.> Hahaha
This place seems strangely familiar. When you first walk in you get this waft of oily plastic smell filling every corner of your mouth. Quickly I become accustomed to it and ask for what I need. State your year, make, model, fule injected?  4door? Blue? 20 inch tires? Plastic engine cover? Once they narrow it down for you they ask what part you are looking for and then show you 4-8 different parts that widely range in price. Well we have a super performance or ultra mega super deluxe package with the difference being $30. I usually pick the one that breaks in a couple of months. Most of my stuff has a lifetime warranty that I don't ever plan on cashing in. I really don't feel like doing my struts again.. let em squeek..<//review>

<userid>114404424526572320809< /userid><Name>Al Mutammara</Name><Date>1539616709400< /Date>< rating>
1<//rating>
< review>
Decided to give this practice a try since they are near my work and my old dentist is in Oakland (I work in Richmond, hassle to go there and back). Initially they seemed like a normal dental practice, the dentist performed an oral exam after X-rays, did a periodontal chart, asked if I have ever done a deep cleaning, said no, and he replied that I won't need one. Identified potential replacement of an older crown that wasn't done properly. Went back few weeks later to do routine teeth cleaning, and the nightmare started. She performed a wishy washy cleaning, said I had some gum cleaning, asked me to come back in 2 weeks to perform a new periodontal chart, so I did. She started to poke very hard into my gum pockets, and produced numbers almost double what their dentist identified couple months prior. She said I have to do a deep cleaning and apply antibiotics to 21 teeth! Cost is a whopping $3700. I laughed and said no way. Went back to my old dentist 3 weeks later for routine cleaning, they found hardly any bleeding and the periodontal chart depths were almost exactly as what the dentist produced at Bright Dental.  I knew the hygienist was a scam. Last month called them to do a routine teeth cleaning (been 6 months), and they replied that they will only do a deep cleaning. Told them I am not interested, and they insisted. SO I went back for another periodontal chart evaluation, and the same hygienist (Harpeet) , showed her numbers and the numbers from my other dentist office, she got defensive , told me if you don't trust us then why come here. Explained to her that I was giving this office a chance to earn my business and find out how could the periodontal chart numbers vary so drastically in less than 3 weeks. She proceeded to redo the chart and this time she was inserting the probe even harder (remember this is inserting a metal probe into gum tissue, insert until you feel resistance, not keep inserting into soft tissue to get extra depth readings). Anyway, she said the numbers are still too deep and she would only do deep cleaning. I requested the dentist, Dr. Wendell came and said ethically they cant perform regular cleaning, told him that I would sign him a waver, do a regular cleaning, he said he trusts the hygienist numbers, even though his own numbers were less by 2-3 mms per reading. He retorted that different operators can get different numbers by 2-3 mms, so essentially the margin of error is 3 mms, so told him if you subtract 3 mms from her readings, then my depths would all be 3 or less, and thus normal. He still claimed its unethical. I told him that you cant force a particular treatment on a patient , we are not in Cuba, and this is coming across as a scam, want to rip patients off. He gave me the spiel that this is not ethical, and he can only do deep cleaning or nothing. I told him I made a mistake coming to this office. I later called their corporate office and complained, they had the office manager call me, explained to her what happened, she insisted that they won't do regular cleaning, only deep cleaning. Cut a long story short, I switched to another dental office nearby, this practice is a rip off, stay away.</review>

<Name>Diane Miller<//Name><date>1524054152381< /date><Rate>4<//Rate>< review>
Came for Little League night. Teams from the surrounding areas get to walk the field with their teams and banners. My grandsons like getting autographs from the players. They are very gracious to the fans and never refuse an autograph or picture. I always enjoy watching the game. There is a playground for the kids that you can purchase either tickets or an all day wristband. The food is pretty good but really pricey, that's why 4 stars. We have been coming to this event for several years and hope to come for many more.< /review>

< Review>
Went here on a Tuesday night when the tickets are BOGO free and also being advertised is a $3 tall can of beer and $3 tacos. 1st off the tall cans were not real tall cans, they are 16 oz. aluminum bottles. Tall cans to me are 24 oz. And all they had were coors light and miller lite for those prices. Even the free coozies the were giving away were for a 24 oz tall can. They ran out of the 3 dollar beers in like the 2nd inning. Then they ran out of tacos in like the 3rd inning. The real tall cans any flavor were available, but those were $10. Still a fun place to go with the kids.<//Review>

< Rate>
2<//Rate>
< text>
Terrible vehicle traffic pattern in and out of stadium.  Seating would have been good had "deck" seats been explained at all on the website.  The "grass" out along the right field foul line is basically a dirt berm.  Not much positive about that area.  When there are a lot of people like the 4th of July all inconvienves are amplified.  Advice for a better experience...go early, buy a regular seat at least a week prior, (do not expect to be comfortable in the grass), expect to pay $5 for parking, $7 for the kid zone experience and expect to spend a lot on concessions, you'll have a much better time knowing these things.</text>

Nice local minor league baseball stadium, (The Storm ) good ole fashion American past time for the whole family...
good parking, but to few entry's and exits, go early ! and allow plenty of time to navigate your way out afterwards.
Aside from the baseball, its also a nice venue for entertainment like concerts, or social events like graduations.
and who can forget the Concessions, Hot Dogs, Beer, and my personal favorite garlic Fry's, just to mention a few of the classic YUMMIES that can be enjoyed here...
and last but not least.. FIREWORKS !!! come and enjoy the fun.</Text>

< review>
Went to Lake Elsinore diamond for a minor league baseball game, home of the Lake Elsinore Storm. The stadium has $5 parking across the street. Inside there are three major food stalls and multiple small vendors. The seats were alright and pretty clean. Restrooms were decently clean for a sports venue. They have specials throughout the week including taco tuesday, free hot dog mondays, and $2 beer Thursdays. You get to sit pretty close to the dugout and home plate for a decent price.<//review>

0x80dc9bb9e4cc6169:0x2a9f2153c55520d2</gmap_id>
<Rate>4< /Rate>< text>
This is a minor league baseball park, home to Lake Elsinore Storm, affiliate of the San Diego Padres. Besides the game itself, entertainment always includes enjoyable skits mostly focusing on kids' participation. Venu is laid out well, partially because attendance is fairly sparse, depending on draw of team's opponents. Parking fee is pretty low and located close to the entrance of the park. And, there are special attractions almost every game like fireworks on many Fridays and flat-out free hot dogs on other days. As a senior riding a motorcycle to the games, there are double savings. Tickets for seats just feet away from home plate are an unbelievable$10. Once inside, PA system announces players' names and other information that doesn't interfere with actual play on the field. Personally, I plan to attend as many games as my schedule allows.< /text>
